<img width="107" height="107" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Babajide-Sanwo-Olu-2-107x107.jpg?resize=107%2C107&#038;ssl=1" alt="Apapa gridlock: Sanwo-Olu reveals fresh plans to build 6,000 capacity truck park" align="left" style="margin: 0 20px 20px 0;max-width:100%" data-recalc-dims="1" /> By Olasunkanmi Akoni – Lagos Lagos State Governor, Mr. Babajide Sanwo-Olu has disclosed plans to construct a 6000-capacity truck park as parts of measures to decongest Apapa axis of perennial traffic gridlock. Sanwo-Olu unveiled this through his twitter handle, Wednesday afternoon. According to the Governor, the state government would also continue to work with the Nigerian Ports Authority and the Nigerian Shipper’s Council to find a permanent solution to the traffic issue in the area. Continue reading Apapa gridlock: Sanwo-Olu reveals fresh plans to build 6,000 capacity truck park at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard